<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Click on Insert â†’ Indicators â†’ Oscillators â†’ Relative Strength Index.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Adjust the Period (default is 14) based on your strategy.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Modify Levels (30 for oversold, 70 for overbought) if needed.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Click OK to apply the RSI indicator to your chart.</span></li>
</ol>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Now, you can use the RSI to identify overbought or oversold conditions and make informed trading decisions directly within MT4.</span></p>
